        "timestamp": 1772722467,
        "contenuto_esteso": "(Adnkronos) - With a bipartisan vote, the House Oversight Committee approved summoning Attorney General Pam Bondi with a subpoena for a closed-door deposition in the investigation into the handling of Jeffrey Epstein's case. The move, which comes after Hillary and Bill Clinton's depositions before the committee last week, had been requested in recent months by lawmakers from both parties after the Department of Justice, led by Bondi, failed for 42 days to meet the deadline for the publication of the Epstein files, set by the law approved last year in Congress."
