        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. War in the Middle East: Where does France stand? Analysis Issued on: 05/03/2026 - 15:44 Share Since US-Israeli strikes against Iran began last Saturday, France has taken what President Emmanuel Macron calls a “strictly defensive” posture. On Tuesday, Macron said the US-Israel operations in Iran were conducted “outside international law”, while announcing the deployment of the aircraft carrier Charles de Gaulle and other military assets to the Mediterranean. So where does France stand? FRANCE 24’s Clovis Casali explains. Video by: Clovis CASALI Iraqi-based Kurdish groups a ‘long-running threat’ to Tehran 05/03/2026 Israel keeps up Lebanon strikes, more than 83,000 people displaced 05/03/2026 Iran pummeled by intensive airstrikes as war enters day six 05/03/2026 'No to Israel': US veteran violently dragged from Senate during protest 05/03/2026 Americas Middle East war spirals as Iran hits Kurds in Iraq 05/03/2026 US Senate blocks resolution that would stop attacks in Iran 05/03/2026 Americas Millions left without power after major blackout hits Cuba 05/03/2026 Americas Israel launches new strikes on Lebanon, at least 72 killed in 4 days 05/03/2026 Forbidden Stories reports on FindFace in Iran: Facial recognition 'an issue' for Western democracies 05/03/2026"
